                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/171: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Dawes</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-14T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 14, 1929—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. Since dictating my number 247, September 14, 4 p.m., I have received your
                    No. 270, September 13, midnight, Mr. MacDonald’s criticism of the agreement.
                    This reenforces my suggestion that we <pb facs="0368" n="232" xml:id="pg_232"/>
                    allow the publication of that agreement to wait until after Mr. MacDonald’s
                    visit. Assuming that this can be done I will not now attempt any review of Mr.
                    MacDonald’s suggestions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
